            <header>
                <h1 class="text-3xl tracking-tight leading-10 font-extrabold text-gray-900 sm:text-4xl sm:leading-none md:text-5xl">
                    About Prosopo
                </h1>
            </header>
            <div class="prose mt-8">
                <p>
                    Prosopo is an open source project dedicated to creating a community powerered bot detection network. Existing bot
                    detection services are either privacy invasive or expensive. We aim to change that by creating a network of websites
                    that can detect bots without compromising user privacy. The more websites that join the network, the more powerful the
                    bot detection becomes.
                </p>
                <p>Our approach to bot detection stems from traditional CAPTCHA systems, but with a twist. We collect as little
                    information on the user as possible, with most detection being run in the browser. Cryptographic proofs are used to send
                    the minimum amount of information to the server, and the server can verify the proof without needing to know anything
                    about the user.
                </p>
                <h2>
                    Trusted by the Web3 Foundation
                </h2>
                <p>
                    Prosopo started after receiving a
                    <a href="https://grants.web3.foundation/applications/prosopo" target="_blank">grant from the Web3 Foundation</a>. The
                        Web3 Foundation is a Swiss foundation that nurtures and stewards technologies and applications in the fields of
                        decentralized web software protocols. The foundation is dedicated to building an internet where users are in control of
                        their own data, identity and destiny.
                </p>
                <img alt="Web 3 Foundation Logo" src="/static/web3-foundation-trimmed.svg" class="w-1/2 h-1/2 mx-auto"></div>
            </article>
